2
00:00:25.095 --> 00:00:29.926
GODZILLA 70TH ANNIVERSARY PRODUCTION

3
00:01:32.061 --> 00:01:32.728
ODO ISLAND NAVY DETACHMENT

4
00:01:32.729 --> 00:01:34.977
- Let's go!
- Heave ho!

5
00:01:37.642 --> 00:01:38.682
Engine normal.

6
00:01:38.683 --> 00:01:39.765
Roger.

7
00:01:39.766 --> 00:01:42.265
- Fuel-system checks out.
- Roger.

8
00:01:50.552 --> 00:01:52.176
Ensign Shikishima?

9
00:01:53.676 --> 00:01:58.008
Tsukuba Naval Air Corps. Tachibana.
Remember me?

10
00:01:58.590 --> 00:02:02.629
{\an8}Of course. I am greatly in your debt.

11
00:02:03.587 --> 00:02:07.917
I'm amazed you were able to land
that bucket of bolts...

12
00:02:07.918 --> 00:02:10.584
on this Swiss cheese of a runway.

13
00:02:11.333 --> 00:02:13.164
{\an8}You haven't lost your touch.

14
00:02:13.165 --> 00:02:18.955
{\an8}In simulated dogfights. no.
but suddenly. I'm a real kamikaze pilot.

15
00:02:20.705 --> 00:02:24.452
Then be grateful for the downtime.

16
00:02:27.201 --> 00:02:28.536
But it's odd.

17
00:02:29.204 --> 00:02:33.377
We've scoured your rig
and can't find anything wrong.

18
00:02:36.756 --> 00:02:38.676
What are you implying?

19
00:03:02.251 --> 00:03:06.298
I'm on your side.
We need more people like you.

20
00:03:13.308 --> 00:03:19.233
Why obey an order to "die honorably"
when the outcome is already clear?

21
00:04:14.939 --> 00:04:17.150
- Get the guns!
- Yes. sir!

22
00:04:18.443 --> 00:04:19.736
- An enemy raid?
- I don't know!

23
00:04:19.737 --> 00:04:22.615
- What is it?
- Something big!

24
00:04:22.616 --> 00:04:24.410
A new Yankee weapon?

25
00:04:29.585 --> 00:04:32.254
Taki! Taki!

26
00:04:32.255 --> 00:04:34.717
- Light the beach!
- Roger!

27
00:04:47.611 --> 00:04:48.945
Taki!

28
00:04:48.946 --> 00:04:50.655
What in the hell?

29
00:04:50.656 --> 00:04:52.575
It's Godzilla.

30
00:04:52.576 --> 00:04:54.953
- What?
- A local told me.

31
00:04:54.954 --> 00:04:57.917
It brings up deep-sea fish.

32
00:04:58.584 --> 00:04:59.920
G-G-Godzilla?

33
00:05:06.262 --> 00:05:08.806
We're screwed. Take cover!

34
00:05:08.807 --> 00:05:11.895
Take cover!

35
00:05:22.035 --> 00:05:24.078
What the hell is it?

36
00:05:24.079 --> 00:05:25.916
Nobody knows.

37
00:05:27.292 --> 00:05:29.587
- Ensign Shikishima.
- Sir.

38
00:05:30.547 --> 00:05:32.633
Can you reach your 20mm gun?

39
00:05:33.551 --> 00:05:36.888
You're our only gunner.
We're just mechanics.

40
00:05:36.889 --> 00:05:40.559
But what if it just makes it angry?

41
00:05:40.560 --> 00:05:43.357
A 20mm gun can kill anything!

42
00:05:44.024 --> 00:05:46.652
Hurry before it gets too close.

43
00:05:46.653 --> 00:05:48.531
Go! Now!

44
00:05:49.282 --> 00:05:50.784
Go.

45
00:05:51.493 --> 00:05:53.078
Hurry.

46
00:06:21.869 --> 00:06:23.120
What's he doing?

47
00:06:31.174 --> 00:06:32.216
Now! Fire!

48
00:06:45.986 --> 00:06:48.114
It's coming this way.

49
00:06:48.782 --> 00:06:51.242
- What do we do. sir?
- Ammo!

50
00:06:51.243 --> 00:06:52.828
Fetch the ammo!

51
00:06:59.672 --> 00:07:01.091
You idiot! Don't shoot!

52
00:07:02.425 --> 00:07:04.219
Cease fire!

53
00:07:04.220 --> 00:07:05.680
Cease firing!

54
00:07:10.228 --> 00:07:12.815
Fall back! Fall back!

55
00:07:12.816 --> 00:07:14.150
Retreat!

56
00:07:19.533 --> 00:07:20.910
Mr. Tachibana!

57
00:08:00.174 --> 00:08:03.636
I'll draw it this way. Shoot to kill!

58
00:09:17.198 --> 00:09:19.534
You guys didn't deserve this.

59
00:09:30.466 --> 00:09:31.593
Hey!

60
00:09:40.272 --> 00:09:42.108
Everybody's dead!

61
00:09:43.943 --> 00:09:45.863
They're all dead...

62
00:09:47.741 --> 00:09:50.453
because you didn't shoot!

63
00:09:55.251 --> 00:09:56.669
Damn it!

64
00:10:35.307 --> 00:10:36.433
You.

65
00:10:37.184 --> 00:10:38.269
Hey!

66
00:11:22.582 --> 00:11:25.962
Watch where you're stepping. man.

67
00:11:34.307 --> 00:11:36.851
Is that you. Koichi?

68
00:11:39.981 --> 00:11:41.440
Sumiko!

69
00:11:41.441 --> 00:11:43.695
How is this possible?

70
00:11:44.446 --> 00:11:47.074
Weren't you a kamikaze pilot?

71
00:11:54.584 --> 00:11:57.255
You have the nerve to show your face?

72
00:11:57.881 --> 00:11:59.467
You're a disgrace!

73
00:12:01.385 --> 00:12:05.183
Look what happened
because of cowards like you!

74
00:12:07.562 --> 00:12:10.023
If you'd all done your duty...

75
00:12:11.066 --> 00:12:13.695
my children wouldn't have died.

76
00:12:22.833 --> 00:12:26.046
Do you know if my parents survived?

77
00:12:33.097 --> 00:12:35.559
Everybody's dead.

78
00:12:37.395 --> 00:12:41.483
This whole place was engulfed in flames.

79
00:12:44.113 --> 00:12:46.157
Your folks too.

80
00:12:49.078 --> 00:12:52.457
My children met the same fate.

81
00:13:05.309 --> 00:13:08.230
MY DEAREST SON. KOICHI...

82
00:13:10.190 --> 00:13:12.235
"Come back alive." right?

83
00:13:15.406 --> 00:13:17.326
That's what you said.

84
00:13:33.390 --> 00:13:35.309
Stop. thief!

85
00:13:35.976 --> 00:13:38.855
Out of my way!

86
00:13:38.856 --> 00:13:42.027
- Move!
- Grab that woman!

87
00:13:44.364 --> 00:13:45.949
- Please!
- What?

88
00:13:46.700 --> 00:13:48.745
Get back here!

89
00:13:52.291 --> 00:13:53.668
What?

90
00:14:22.166 --> 00:14:23.584
Hey!

91
00:14:27.215 --> 00:14:29.510
Finally. Where did you go?

92
00:14:30.595 --> 00:14:33.347
It's your fault
for sitting out in the open.

93
00:14:33.348 --> 00:14:35.184
I would have been seen.

94
00:14:35.853 --> 00:14:37.939
You've been here the whole time?

95
00:14:39.024 --> 00:14:43.739
Yeah. waiting for you to get up and move.

96
00:14:44.322 --> 00:14:46.617
I bet you're hungry.

97
00:14:49.413 --> 00:14:51.791
Why didn't you just abandon her?

98
00:14:52.751 --> 00:14:53.794
Hey!

99
00:14:55.547 --> 00:14:59.092
And leave her in a place like that?

100
00:15:01.263 --> 00:15:02.347
No?

101
00:15:04.017 --> 00:15:05.895
Interesting.

102
00:15:09.107 --> 00:15:11.318
Please don't follow me.

103
00:15:11.319 --> 00:15:14.155
Are you going to leave us
to die on the street?

104
00:15:14.156 --> 00:15:15.491
I don't care.

105
00:15:21.412 --> 00:15:24.372
After you're done. you're leaving.

106
00:15:24.373 --> 00:15:27.918
Hear that? He's so mean and scary.

107
00:15:31.463 --> 00:15:33.588
Where's your husband?

108
00:15:33.589 --> 00:15:35.299
Is he a soldier?

109
00:15:36.342 --> 00:15:39.301
Do I look like I'd have a husband?

110
00:15:39.302 --> 00:15:40.470
What?

111
00:15:41.180 --> 00:15:42.514
Whose kid is she?

112
00:15:44.099 --> 00:15:47.185
- Does it matter?
- Of course. it does!

113
00:15:50.729 --> 00:15:52.898
During the air raids...

114
00:15:54.148 --> 00:15:56.609
her dying mother begged me.

115
00:15:58.360 --> 00:15:59.362
So you...

116
00:16:00.154 --> 00:16:02.697
have no relation to that child?

117
00:16:04.073 --> 00:16:05.367
Nope. So what?

118
00:16:08.244 --> 00:16:09.912
What are you. stupid?

119
00:16:10.538 --> 00:16:13.664
You're in no state to care for a baby.

120
00:16:13.665 --> 00:16:16.709
You couldn't leave her either.

121
00:16:23.090 --> 00:16:23.924
Name?

122
00:16:27.802 --> 00:16:29.678
AKIKO

123
00:16:29.679 --> 00:16:32.806
No. I meant you.

124
00:16:35.059 --> 00:16:36.184
Noriko.

125
00:16:39.395 --> 00:16:43.774
Why do you dress like a vagrant?
By choice?

126
00:16:44.567 --> 00:16:46.025
Well. I'm no harlot.

127
00:16:46.026 --> 00:16:48.112
Don't look insulted.

128
00:16:49.404 --> 00:16:52.949
You've got to survive somehow.
Who could blame you?

129
00:16:59.204 --> 00:17:00.539
What about family?

130
00:17:09.087 --> 00:17:10.547
HARU SHIKISHIMA - EIICHIRO SHIKISHIMA

131
00:17:10.548 --> 00:17:11.882
Your parents?

132
00:17:16.469 --> 00:17:17.511
Yeah.

133
00:17:19.013 --> 00:17:22.516
They were killed in the air raids.

134
00:17:26.686 --> 00:17:28.646
Then you and I are the same.

135
00:17:48.038 --> 00:17:48.872
What?

136
00:17:48.873 --> 00:17:51.333
No. you can't...

137
00:17:52.917 --> 00:17:55.169
stay...

138
00:18:08.472 --> 00:18:09.932
Hey!

139
00:18:11.891 --> 00:18:13.726
What's the story?

140
00:18:15.102 --> 00:18:18.230
- What do you mean?
- Don't play dumb.

141
00:18:18.813 --> 00:18:21.398
The mother and child you picked up.

142
00:18:21.399 --> 00:18:24.235
Think you're some kind of saint?

143
00:18:24.236 --> 00:18:25.402
No.

144
00:18:25.986 --> 00:18:28.072
They just showed up.

145
00:18:28.822 --> 00:18:31.866
If they're staying. you picked them up.

146
00:18:36.162 --> 00:18:38.581
It's a bit late to play the hero.

147
00:18:40.041 --> 00:18:44.252
Count me out. I'm done caring.

148
00:18:49.173 --> 00:18:50.424
Wait.

149
00:18:51.592 --> 00:18:54.302
Is that girl able to breastfeed?

150
00:18:56.264 --> 00:19:01.308
No. She's not the child's mother.

151
00:19:02.227 --> 00:19:03.435
What?

152
00:19:16.071 --> 00:19:19.406
At this rate. she'll die of malnutrition.

153
00:19:19.407 --> 00:19:20.617
Right?

154
00:19:21.451 --> 00:19:26.289
So you found a child.
but you have no idea how to care for it.

155
00:19:26.914 --> 00:19:28.623
What were you thinking?

156
00:19:29.624 --> 00:19:31.042
I don't know.

157
00:19:39.383 --> 00:19:41.135
It's not for you.

158
00:19:42.427 --> 00:19:44.804
Adults can survive on anything.

159
00:19:50.143 --> 00:19:52.227
Use it to make rice gruel.

160
00:19:53.228 --> 00:19:54.103
Well...

161
00:19:55.062 --> 00:19:57.648
there goes my prized white rice.

162
00:19:58.858 --> 00:20:01.067
What a nuisance. I swear.

163
00:20:12.411 --> 00:20:16.581
Damn it. I'm soaking wet.

164
00:20:23.045 --> 00:20:24.629
Was there any work?

165
00:20:25.882 --> 00:20:28.966
Well. I did find something.

166
00:20:28.967 --> 00:20:30.426
What's the matter?

167
00:20:32.137 --> 00:20:34.387
The money's not bad either.

168
00:20:34.388 --> 00:20:38.475
Look. They even paid an advance
of 3.000 yen.

169
00:20:38.476 --> 00:20:40.643
That's wonderful!

170
00:20:45.106 --> 00:20:50.026
It must be a scam.
like the rice you carried that got stolen.

171
00:20:50.027 --> 00:20:52.569
It's nothing like that.

172
00:20:52.570 --> 00:20:54.696
What makes you so sure?

173
00:20:54.697 --> 00:20:57.824
It's government approved.

174
00:20:57.825 --> 00:21:00.659
There's a reason why it pays well.

175
00:21:00.660 --> 00:21:01.869
Like what?

176
00:21:01.870 --> 00:21:07.833
During the war. both sides laid
thousands of mines in the sea.

177
00:21:08.626 --> 00:21:09.794
This is a cleanup job.

178
00:21:11.920 --> 00:21:15.382
But the pay is extremely good
because. well...

179
00:21:18.258 --> 00:21:22.513
it comes with a certain amount of risk.

180
00:21:24.222 --> 00:21:27.557
What are you. crazy?
You just survived a war!

181
00:21:27.558 --> 00:21:29.643
What else can I do?

182
00:21:29.644 --> 00:21:33.605
At this rate. we'll starve.
Akiko's life depends on it.

183
00:21:35.399 --> 00:21:38.902
I understand that but...

184
00:21:40.736 --> 00:21:42.239
This brings in money.

185
00:21:42.863 --> 00:21:46.907
With money. we can even buy
American powdered milk!

186
00:21:46.908 --> 00:21:47.826
For that. I'd do...

187
00:21:48.953 --> 00:21:50.912
I forbid you to die!

188
00:21:55.125 --> 00:22:00.421
Don't worry. Just because it's dangerous
doesn't mean I'll die.

189
00:22:01.630 --> 00:22:04.132
It's not like being a kamikaze pilot.

190
00:22:08.969 --> 00:22:10.302
And besides...

191
00:22:10.303 --> 00:22:14.266
I'll be on a special boat
made to evade mines.

192
00:22:18.811 --> 00:22:22.021
This is specially made?

193
00:22:36.160 --> 00:22:38.785
Hey. are you our new sharpshooter?

194
00:22:38.786 --> 00:22:39.786
I'm Shikishima.

195
00:22:39.787 --> 00:22:40.704
Sailor?

196
00:22:40.705 --> 00:22:42.038
Fighter pilot.

197
00:22:42.039 --> 00:22:44.582
What? This guy's useless.

198
00:22:44.583 --> 00:22:46.000
You're an ex-airman?

199
00:22:46.001 --> 00:22:48.295
Just a military castoff. Worthless.

200
00:22:49.171 --> 00:22:51.296
Disappointed?

201
00:22:51.297 --> 00:22:53.549
When seeing this boat?

202
00:22:54.133 --> 00:22:58.677
The US and Imperial navies laid
60.000 mines off Japan's coasts.

203
00:22:58.678 --> 00:23:03.681
all kinds. but the worst are
the American magnetic mines.

204
00:23:03.682 --> 00:23:07.811
Any approaching boat made of metal
sets them off.

205
00:23:09.645 --> 00:23:11.731
Ah. hence the wood.

206
00:23:11.732 --> 00:23:14.649
The boy catches on fast.

207
00:23:14.650 --> 00:23:17.277
We mostly handle moored mines.

208
00:23:17.278 --> 00:23:21.114
But wood boats are
the best countermeasure.

209
00:23:23.492 --> 00:23:24.618
I'm Noda.

210
00:23:25.367 --> 00:23:29.287
I developed naval weapons during the war.

211
00:23:29.288 --> 00:23:31.914
Boat captain Akitsu and Mizushima.

212
00:23:31.915 --> 00:23:33.582
"The Kid" and "Doc".

213
00:23:33.583 --> 00:23:35.959
I'm not fond of that nickname.

214
00:23:35.960 --> 00:23:37.836
And I'm not a "kid".

215
00:23:37.837 --> 00:23:40.379
You're still green. so "Kid" it is.

216
00:23:40.380 --> 00:23:43.674
I know. I wasn't in the war.

217
00:23:43.675 --> 00:23:48.553
This is a mine sweeper. the Shinseimaru.
It's paired with the Kaishinmaru.

218
00:23:48.554 --> 00:23:53.683
The mines rise up from the seabed
like balloons on strings.

219
00:23:53.684 --> 00:23:57.477
Between our two boats
is a cable with a cutter.

220
00:23:57.478 --> 00:24:00.232
All we do is clip the mine wire.

221
00:24:01.023 --> 00:24:02.690
and it floats to the surface.

222
00:24:02.691 --> 00:24:07.487
Then we fire on it with this baby.
rat-tat-tat-tat.

223
00:24:08.321 --> 00:24:09.447
Take a look.

224
00:24:20.957 --> 00:24:23.166
This one's a bit tricky.

225
00:24:23.167 --> 00:24:24.919
May I give it a try?

226
00:24:25.545 --> 00:24:26.962
Are you sure?

227
00:24:31.758 --> 00:24:37.513
You have to estimate its position
and account for movement.

228
00:24:44.018 --> 00:24:45.310
Woo-hoo!

229
00:24:46.896 --> 00:24:48.729
Nice shot!

230
00:24:48.730 --> 00:24:50.565
Same with fighter planes.

231
00:24:50.566 --> 00:24:53.067
Not that I saw any real action.

232
00:24:53.068 --> 00:24:54.194
What?

233
00:24:55.027 --> 00:24:59.447
You didn't? That makes me
and Shikishima equals.

234
00:24:59.448 --> 00:25:02.241
Hardly. You can't fly a plane.

235
00:25:02.242 --> 00:25:05.619
If I'd gone to war. I would've learned.

236
00:25:05.620 --> 00:25:08.080
If only it had lasted longer.

237
00:25:11.083 --> 00:25:13.294
You'd better not mean that.

238
00:25:16.338 --> 00:25:17.297
No. sorry.

239
00:25:21.718 --> 00:25:23.052
You fool.

240
00:25:53.536 --> 00:25:55.495
Fire! Fire! Fall back!

241
00:26:13.428 --> 00:26:14.846
You all right?

242
00:26:22.019 --> 00:26:23.604
Another bad dream?

243
00:26:31.568 --> 00:26:32.737
A dream.

244
00:26:36.365 --> 00:26:37.573
Right.

245
00:26:38.992 --> 00:26:41.077
I was dreaming.

246
00:26:48.291 --> 00:26:49.668
Or maybe...

247
00:26:51.086 --> 00:26:53.670
you're just a dream.

248
00:26:53.671 --> 00:26:56.339
- What's wrong with you?
- Tell me.

249
00:26:56.340 --> 00:26:58.466
This is Japan. right?

250
00:26:58.467 --> 00:27:01.551
I really did return alive. right?

251
00:27:01.552 --> 00:27:03.805
- I returned alive!
- Stop!

252
00:27:24.656 --> 00:27:25.907
Yes. I know.

253
00:27:26.574 --> 00:27:27.784
I know.

254
00:27:29.576 --> 00:27:31.078
I know.

255
00:28:38.011 --> 00:28:39.761
Nice place you built here.

256
00:28:39.762 --> 00:28:41.471
Worth every penny saved.

257
00:28:41.472 --> 00:28:42.555
SHIKISHIMA

258
00:28:47.226 --> 00:28:48.601
Drink?

259
00:28:48.602 --> 00:28:50.938
Oh. why. thank you.

260
00:28:54.107 --> 00:28:55.609
May I take a photo?

261
00:28:56.401 --> 00:29:00.153
- Please don't waste your film.
- That smile!

262
00:29:00.154 --> 00:29:02.781
Hold it. Hold it.

263
00:29:02.782 --> 00:29:03.949
Ready?

264
00:29:06.493 --> 00:29:07.910
- Thank you.
- Hey. Doc.

265
00:29:07.911 --> 00:29:09.870
No coveting now.

266
00:29:09.871 --> 00:29:13.582
Of course not. Noriko's a married woman.

267
00:29:13.583 --> 00:29:15.374
Please stop.

268
00:29:15.375 --> 00:29:17.502
I'm not a wife.

269
00:29:20.671 --> 00:29:21.756
What does that mean?

270
00:29:22.298 --> 00:29:25.008
She just moved in on her own.

271
00:29:25.009 --> 00:29:28.303
She had no place to go. so I let her stay.

272
00:29:29.179 --> 00:29:30.471
And the child?

273
00:29:30.472 --> 00:29:34.766
She brought her too.
But they aren't related.

274
00:29:34.767 --> 00:29:38.354
Akiko was orphaned in the air raids.

275
00:29:40.021 --> 00:29:43.065
- Wow. that's a beautiful story.
- No.

276
00:29:43.066 --> 00:29:45.276
It just sort of happened.

277
00:29:47.694 --> 00:29:48.946
Daddy.

278
00:29:51.198 --> 00:29:53.407
- Akiko.
- What?

279
00:29:54.201 --> 00:29:56.828
I told you. I'm not your father.

280
00:29:59.371 --> 00:30:01.122
Shikishima.

281
00:30:01.123 --> 00:30:03.917
- Don't say that.
- That's truly harmful.

282
00:30:05.167 --> 00:30:09.379
Fate has brought you together as a family.

283
00:30:09.380 --> 00:30:10.964
Accept it. Embrace it.

284
00:30:10.965 --> 00:30:13.759
Make them happy!

285
00:30:14.759 --> 00:30:15.927
Enough!

286
00:30:16.636 --> 00:30:18.388
I don't want that.

287
00:30:24.102 --> 00:30:25.561
Why not?

288
00:30:40.948 --> 00:30:43.909
Welcome home. I just returned myself.

289
00:30:44.493 --> 00:30:45.661
What are you wearing?

290
00:30:49.623 --> 00:30:50.623
How does it look?

291
00:30:51.291 --> 00:30:53.292
I got a desk job in Ginza.

292
00:30:53.293 --> 00:30:56.545
But don't I give you enough money?

293
00:31:02.717 --> 00:31:05.720
It's time I stood on my own two feet.

294
00:31:06.929 --> 00:31:10.348
At this rate. you'll never find a wife.

295
00:31:14.227 --> 00:31:17.564
Have you seen how fast
Ginza is rebuilding?

296
00:31:18.814 --> 00:31:19.732
This is so sudden.

297
00:31:20.941 --> 00:31:22.400
Not for me. it isn't.

298
00:31:23.861 --> 00:31:25.486
What about Akiko?

299
00:31:26.362 --> 00:31:31.992
What will you do with Akiko
while you are away at work?

300
00:31:32.576 --> 00:31:35.746
Sumiko has promised to look after her.

301
00:31:37.122 --> 00:31:41.876
She was very excited.
boasting she'd raised three kids already.

302
00:31:44.628 --> 00:31:48.006
In that case. I suppose it's all right.

303
00:31:49.257 --> 00:31:52.051
Thanks. I'll go get Akiko now.

304
00:32:32.919 --> 00:32:36.964
<i>The colossal sea creature is projected
on a course</i>

305
00:32:36.965 --> 00:32:41.511
<i>to reach the Japanese archipelago
within a few weeks.</i>

306
00:32:43.470 --> 00:32:47.431
<i>General Douglas MacArthur
stated with regret</i>

307
00:32:47.432 --> 00:32:52.852
<i>that recent Soviet movements prevent
US military assistance</i>

308
00:32:52.853 --> 00:32:55.437
<i>but called upon Japan</i>

309
00:32:55.438 --> 00:32:59.359
<i>to begin strengthening
its security forces.</i>

310
00:33:12.578 --> 00:33:14.246
What did this?

311
00:33:15.122 --> 00:33:17.290
A giant shark?

312
00:33:18.291 --> 00:33:19.375
Or a whale?

313
00:33:19.376 --> 00:33:22.546
No shark or whale could do that.

314
00:33:23.629 --> 00:33:25.130
A new Soviet weapon?

315
00:33:25.131 --> 00:33:27.131
That's not weapon damage.

316
00:33:27.132 --> 00:33:28.801
Then what could it be?

317
00:33:29.510 --> 00:33:32.095
- An enormous creature.
- Like what?

318
00:33:32.928 --> 00:33:35.222
Just admit you have no clue.

319
00:33:35.223 --> 00:33:38.350
I was skeptical until I saw this.

320
00:33:40.978 --> 00:33:41.812
Godzilla.

321
00:33:44.647 --> 00:33:45.732
Look there!

322
00:33:49.401 --> 00:33:51.153
Floating deep-sea fish.

323
00:33:51.154 --> 00:33:53.572
Just like on Odo Island.

324
00:33:54.281 --> 00:33:56.239
What did you see there?

325
00:33:56.240 --> 00:34:00.994
It was like
a prehistoric dinosaur-turned-monster.

326
00:34:00.995 --> 00:34:05.040
The local inhabitants
called it "Godzilla."

327
00:34:05.749 --> 00:34:07.082
Godzilla?

328
00:34:07.083 --> 00:34:10.669
Nonsense. You were half asleep
and saw an enemy tank.

329
00:34:10.670 --> 00:34:14.590
Whether you believe me or not.
something wiped out...

330
00:34:15.299 --> 00:34:17.551
the entire garrison on Odo.

331
00:34:18.259 --> 00:34:19.552
Hold on.

332
00:34:20.219 --> 00:34:22.388
I thought the Americans did that.

333
00:34:24.306 --> 00:34:28.225
Odo was never targeted
by US island-hopping forces.

334
00:34:28.226 --> 00:34:32.063
It was a repair base for kamikaze planes.

335
00:34:33.356 --> 00:34:34.690
Does that mean...

336
00:34:35.816 --> 00:34:37.484
you were a kamikaze pilot?

337
00:34:44.073 --> 00:34:46.450
If this is the same Godzilla I saw...

338
00:34:47.284 --> 00:34:51.038
it must have grown
much larger and more powerful.

339
00:34:56.834 --> 00:34:58.377
Hold on a second.

340
00:34:59.045 --> 00:35:02.506
Why were we called out here to begin with?

341
00:35:03.340 --> 00:35:07.467
They don't expect us to fight that
in this boat!

342
00:35:07.468 --> 00:35:09.260
Yes. they do.

343
00:35:09.261 --> 00:35:12.638
We obviously don't stand a chance!

344
00:35:12.639 --> 00:35:17.392
That's a US warship!
What can we do in this little rig?

345
00:35:17.393 --> 00:35:19.520
Stall for time.

346
00:35:20.480 --> 00:35:21.896
Stall?

347
00:35:21.897 --> 00:35:25.357
The Takao is coming from Singapore.

348
00:35:25.358 --> 00:35:27.485
The heavy cruiser?

349
00:35:27.486 --> 00:35:31.155
Rather than scuttle it.
it's being returned.

350
00:35:31.823 --> 00:35:34.366
That's good news! The Takao's a beast!

351
00:35:34.367 --> 00:35:38.244
So we've been ordered to stall for time.

352
00:35:38.245 --> 00:35:42.622
Why can't the US handle it?
It's their ship.

353
00:35:42.623 --> 00:35:45.792
They're worried about the Soviets.

354
00:35:45.793 --> 00:35:49.420
Any military maneuvers would raise alarms.

355
00:35:49.421 --> 00:35:52.714
They'd prefer we handle the small stuff.

356
00:35:52.715 --> 00:35:56.593
This isn't small stuff.
and all we've got is a 13mm gun.

357
00:35:56.594 --> 00:36:00.221
I was told to make use of recovered mines.

358
00:36:00.972 --> 00:36:05.183
Ah. now I see!
This is why they called us out here.

359
00:36:05.184 --> 00:36:09.479
Plus. our main weapon has to be
locally scavenged?

360
00:36:09.480 --> 00:36:13.649
We're also not allowed
to talk about it with anyone.

361
00:36:13.650 --> 00:36:17.153
There it is. Their favorite gag order.

362
00:36:18.237 --> 00:36:20.573
This country never changes.

363
00:36:21.615 --> 00:36:23.116
Perhaps. it can't.

364
00:36:32.583 --> 00:36:34.168
Take a breather.

365
00:36:36.460 --> 00:36:38.046
Thank you.

366
00:36:38.713 --> 00:36:40.590
Don't push yourself too hard.

367
00:36:41.840 --> 00:36:44.635
I can't help it. This is Godzilla.

368
00:36:46.553 --> 00:36:51.515
I hear you.
When I start remembering the war...

369
00:36:52.474 --> 00:36:54.810
I can't sleep sometimes.

370
00:36:55.644 --> 00:36:57.686
I have to avenge them.

371
00:36:57.687 --> 00:36:59.606
But at the same time...

372
00:37:00.482 --> 00:37:02.775
I'm terrified of that thing.

373
00:37:08.780 --> 00:37:12.826
We'll need more than a pair of those.

374
00:37:18.998 --> 00:37:20.207
What is it?

375
00:37:38.598 --> 00:37:42.768
There are way more of these fish
than I saw off Odo.

376
00:37:45.895 --> 00:37:48.689
Sound the alarm!

377
00:37:48.690 --> 00:37:50.148
Godzilla's coming!

378
00:37:50.149 --> 00:37:52.275
Sound the alarm!

379
00:37:53.693 --> 00:37:56.070
So it's coming. huh?

380
00:37:56.071 --> 00:37:58.821
Hey. Kid! Prepare to drop the mines!

381
00:37:58.822 --> 00:38:00.491
- Roger!
- Man the gun!

382
00:38:00.492 --> 00:38:03.284
We can't fight it on this!

383
00:38:03.285 --> 00:38:05.870
- We can still flee!
- Agreed.

384
00:38:05.871 --> 00:38:08.538
- Doc. stand aft and report!
- Captain!

385
00:38:08.539 --> 00:38:11.083
Kaishinmaru. do you copy?

386
00:38:11.084 --> 00:38:14.253
Get ready to land a big one!

387
00:38:14.254 --> 00:38:17.213
<i>We're taking all the credit for victory.</i>

388
00:38:17.214 --> 00:38:18.589
- You idiot.
- Captain!

389
00:38:18.590 --> 00:38:21.675
If we run. the Takao will never catch up.

390
00:38:21.676 --> 00:38:24.178
and the monster will head for Tokyo.

391
00:38:25.346 --> 00:38:28.055
I don't want to see it in flames again.

392
00:38:28.056 --> 00:38:30.516
But this boat is no match for it!

393
00:38:30.517 --> 00:38:33.227
I thought you hated government orders.

394
00:38:33.228 --> 00:38:36.855
With a passion. But you know what?

395
00:38:37.481 --> 00:38:39.566
Somebody's got to do it.

396
00:38:56.497 --> 00:38:59.125
Okay. never mind!

397
00:39:03.336 --> 00:39:04.628
Doc. the engine!

398
00:39:04.629 --> 00:39:06.630
I'm working on it!

399
00:39:06.631 --> 00:39:08.258
Shikishima!

400
00:39:09.466 --> 00:39:10.509
Shikishima!

401
00:39:11.511 --> 00:39:13.387
Hurry! Over here!

402
00:39:14.888 --> 00:39:17.348
- Captain!
- I know!

403
00:39:17.349 --> 00:39:19.350
- Full throttle!
- Right!

404
00:39:40.201 --> 00:39:41.953
Drop the mines!

405
00:39:43.121 --> 00:39:44.996
We'll never make it!

406
00:39:44.997 --> 00:39:47.207
We gotta try something!

407
00:40:06.807 --> 00:40:08.183
Now. Kid!

408
00:40:08.184 --> 00:40:10.102
Here goes!

409
00:40:15.856 --> 00:40:17.067
Did we get it?

410
00:40:23.238 --> 00:40:24.989
No. we did not!

411
00:40:24.990 --> 00:40:27.741
Bad. bad. bad...

412
00:40:27.742 --> 00:40:28.992
Shikishima. the gun!

413
00:40:28.993 --> 00:40:30.495
Roger!

414
00:40:38.334 --> 00:40:39.210
Shikishima!

415
00:40:50.220 --> 00:40:52.263
Completely ineffective!

416
00:40:56.183 --> 00:40:59.520
The mouth! What about in the mouth?

417
00:41:01.354 --> 00:41:05.649
Reel! Reel!

418
00:41:05.650 --> 00:41:07.317
Drop it!

419
00:41:14.115 --> 00:41:16.575
Mizushima. now!

420
00:41:16.576 --> 00:41:17.493
Right!

421
00:41:26.458 --> 00:41:29.045
What? No.

422
00:41:29.711 --> 00:41:30.546
No!

423
00:41:42.722 --> 00:41:45.143
Get down!

424
00:42:08.202 --> 00:42:09.580
Did we get it?

425
00:42:17.669 --> 00:42:18.587
No!

426
00:42:43.774 --> 00:42:45.568
The Takao!

427
00:42:45.569 --> 00:42:46.694
They made it!

428
00:43:15.260 --> 00:43:16.220
Oh. no.

429
00:43:53.834 --> 00:43:54.835
Is it down?

430
00:44:06.345 --> 00:44:07.180
What's that?

431
00:45:08.190 --> 00:45:09.734
You're finally awake.

432
00:45:11.985 --> 00:45:13.070
Where am I?

433
00:45:13.903 --> 00:45:17.323
A Yokosuka hospital.
We were transported here.

434
00:45:18.908 --> 00:45:21.702
What of the Kaishinmaru and the Takao?

435
00:45:28.374 --> 00:45:29.666
Godzilla.

436
00:45:30.251 --> 00:45:32.877
What happened to it?

437
00:45:32.878 --> 00:45:35.588
Whereabouts unknown.

438
00:45:35.589 --> 00:45:39.883
It was headed for Tokyo.
We need to sound the evacuation order.

439
00:45:39.884 --> 00:45:43.512
The government is not telling the public.

440
00:45:44.180 --> 00:45:45.846
Why? We must hurry!

441
00:45:45.847 --> 00:45:48.682
To prevent mayhem and confusion.

442
00:45:48.683 --> 00:45:52.644
Are you kidding me?
We need to begin evacuating now!

443
00:45:52.645 --> 00:45:55.481
No one will take responsibility...

444
00:45:56.231 --> 00:45:57.565
for the chaos.

445
00:45:57.566 --> 00:46:00.527
Information control is Japan's specialty.

446
00:46:09.451 --> 00:46:11.452
Tell me what happened.

447
00:46:13.080 --> 00:46:15.873
It's got nothing to do with you.

448
00:46:17.917 --> 00:46:20.710
What is it that torments you so badly?

449
00:46:23.046 --> 00:46:27.590
You took me in. saved me.
and we've been together since.

450
00:46:27.591 --> 00:46:31.679
But you won't let me
into any part of your life.

451
00:46:38.851 --> 00:46:41.270
If you're carrying some burden...

452
00:46:42.313 --> 00:46:44.606
I wish you'd share it with me.

453
00:46:56.616 --> 00:46:57.867
I'm...

454
00:46:59.953 --> 00:47:00.995
someone...

455
00:47:11.463 --> 00:47:12.839
who fled his duty...

456
00:47:17.343 --> 00:47:18.760
as a kamikaze pilot.

457
00:47:20.470 --> 00:47:21.303
What?

458
00:47:22.096 --> 00:47:23.807
On the day of my sortie...

459
00:47:26.517 --> 00:47:28.894
I pretended my plane was faulty...

460
00:47:31.229 --> 00:47:32.897
and made a detour...

461
00:47:34.106 --> 00:47:36.109
landing on Odo Island.

462
00:47:49.120 --> 00:47:50.454
These are photos...

463
00:47:51.830 --> 00:47:56.001
belonging to the mechanics there.

464
00:47:58.545 --> 00:48:01.922
They all perished.

465
00:48:15.517 --> 00:48:16.560
That night...

466
00:48:18.520 --> 00:48:21.982
a dinosaur-like monster came ashore.

467
00:48:25.567 --> 00:48:26.735
I was asked...

468
00:48:27.527 --> 00:48:30.530
to shoot it with the gun on my fighter.

469
00:48:33.532 --> 00:48:34.867
But I froze up...

470
00:48:40.164 --> 00:48:41.998
and ran again.

471
00:48:43.583 --> 00:48:46.711
When I came to the next day...

472
00:48:47.711 --> 00:48:52.174
I found them all dead.
People longing to see their families!

473
00:48:57.260 --> 00:48:58.638
The monster...

474
00:49:01.306 --> 00:49:03.183
was called Godzilla.

475
00:49:07.603 --> 00:49:10.898
The other day. it reappeared.

476
00:49:13.650 --> 00:49:15.402
And once again...

477
00:49:17.654 --> 00:49:19.947
I couldn't do anything.

478
00:49:29.247 --> 00:49:30.873
I'm someone...

479
00:49:32.666 --> 00:49:35.127
who wasn't supposed to live.

480
00:49:41.842 --> 00:49:43.175
Listen to me.

481
00:49:45.594 --> 00:49:49.763
Everyone who survived the war
is meant to live.

482
00:49:49.764 --> 00:49:53.059
- How do you know?
- I just do!

483
00:49:54.018 --> 00:49:57.856
As flames took my parents.
they ordered me to live.

484
00:49:58.689 --> 00:50:02.818
So whatever happens next.
I know I must survive!

485
00:50:04.069 --> 00:50:05.486
That has kept me going.

486
00:50:18.330 --> 00:50:19.707
I can't.

487
00:50:22.543 --> 00:50:26.753
They beckon to me in my dreams
every night.

488
00:50:26.754 --> 00:50:28.882
"Hurry and come." they say.

489
00:50:29.716 --> 00:50:33.010
"Why are you still cheating death?"

490
00:50:33.011 --> 00:50:37.387
It's just a dream.
just ghosts you created.

491
00:50:37.388 --> 00:50:39.724
Maybe it's an illusion.

492
00:50:40.558 --> 00:50:43.685
What if I'm actually dead already?

493
00:50:45.605 --> 00:50:47.606
I died long ago on that island...

494
00:50:48.231 --> 00:50:49.607
and lie rotting.

495
00:50:50.442 --> 00:50:56.696
You and Akiko are
just the last dream of a dead man.

496
00:50:56.697 --> 00:50:59.239
That must be it! It has to be!

497
00:50:59.240 --> 00:51:01.284
You are alive!

498
00:51:05.412 --> 00:51:07.749
You are alive. Koichi.

499
00:51:11.542 --> 00:51:13.169
Can't you feel it?

500
00:51:27.140 --> 00:51:30.516
Okay. hold the spoon.

501
00:51:30.517 --> 00:51:33.936
Gently.

502
00:51:33.937 --> 00:51:35.980
- Grip it firmly.
- Okay.

503
00:51:37.065 --> 00:51:41.526
Good. now stir the broth.
You're doing great!

504
00:51:42.486 --> 00:51:45.238
- There. it's done!
- Yeah!

505
00:51:46.448 --> 00:51:49.074
I added your favorite. radish.

506
00:51:49.075 --> 00:51:51.534
- Radish!
- Taste it for me.

507
00:51:51.535 --> 00:51:53.703
- Okay.
- Are you ready?

508
00:51:56.373 --> 00:51:58.625
First the soup. then radish.

509
00:52:11.386 --> 00:52:12.386
Can I...

510
00:52:14.847 --> 00:52:16.848
put this all to rest?

511
00:52:23.813 --> 00:52:25.982
I'd like to try to live again.

512
00:52:44.831 --> 00:52:47.666
Is that what I think it is?

513
00:52:48.459 --> 00:52:50.586
Hurry and report it.

514
00:52:51.461 --> 00:52:53.045
Hurry!

515
00:52:53.046 --> 00:52:54.046
Yes. sir!

516
00:53:14.857 --> 00:53:19.818
Patrols report the creature
is heading east toward Tokyo Bay.

517
00:53:19.819 --> 00:53:21.946
Is it close then?

518
00:53:24.157 --> 00:53:26.157
- What is it?
- I don't believe it.

519
00:53:26.158 --> 00:53:27.658
Is it here?

520
00:53:27.659 --> 00:53:30.454
Is that really a living thing?

521
00:53:32.621 --> 00:53:38.084
This is Tokyo Bay Defense.
requesting permission to detonate Zone 4!

522
00:53:38.085 --> 00:53:40.128
It's almost here.

523
00:53:44.257 --> 00:53:46.216
Entering Zone 4!

524
00:53:47.009 --> 00:53:48.385
- Now!
- Detonate!

525
00:53:51.637 --> 00:53:52.472
Status?

526
00:53:53.724 --> 00:53:54.558
No good.

527
00:53:54.559 --> 00:53:56.808
It had no effect!

528
00:53:56.809 --> 00:54:00.313
Blockade breached!
It's heading to Shinagawa!

529
00:54:00.897 --> 00:54:02.856
And it is gargantuan!

530
00:54:05.942 --> 00:54:07.069
Oops.

531
00:54:08.152 --> 00:54:10.196
Thank you.

532
00:54:22.664 --> 00:54:26.084
<i>This is an emergency news report!</i>

533
00:54:26.085 --> 00:54:30.629
<i>A giant sea creature
has come ashore near Ginza.</i>

534
00:54:30.630 --> 00:54:35.343
<i>Those near Ginza.
follow police instructions and evacuate.</i>

535
00:54:36.177 --> 00:54:38.220
- <i>This is not a hoax.</i>
- Ginza!

536
00:54:45.518 --> 00:54:47.436
Are you hurt? You okay?

537
00:55:22.006 --> 00:55:23.133
What's going on?

538
00:55:23.134 --> 00:55:24.926
What just happened?

539
00:55:42.692 --> 00:55:45.610
Is that... Godzilla?

540
00:57:03.677 --> 00:57:09.349
It's a scene that defies belief.
A giant creature on the loose.

541
00:57:09.350 --> 00:57:11.976
trampling Ginza underfoot!

542
00:57:13.310 --> 00:57:16.187
Tearing whole buildings apart!

543
00:57:16.188 --> 00:57:20.565
The Nippon Theater.
beloved icon of the people.

544
00:57:20.566 --> 00:57:23.236
is crumbling before our very eyes!

545
00:57:23.819 --> 00:57:29.114
The Ginza survived air raids but not this!

546
00:57:29.115 --> 00:57:31.408
This monster has turned it to rubble!

547
00:57:31.409 --> 00:57:35.453
And now the monster is coming this way!

548
00:57:35.454 --> 00:57:40.625
I can see its enormous head
passing in front of us!

549
00:57:40.626 --> 00:57:43.503
It's dangerously close!

550
00:58:07.648 --> 00:58:09.025
Move!

551
00:58:17.699 --> 00:58:18.991
Get up!

552
00:58:18.992 --> 00:58:22.370
- Koichi!
- Do you want to live? Come on!

553
00:59:06.407 --> 00:59:07.784
Did they get it?

554
00:59:50.320 --> 00:59:51.613
This is...

555
00:59:52.822 --> 00:59:54.073
the same as before.

556
01:00:48.327 --> 01:00:49.413
Noriko.

557
01:00:51.872 --> 01:00:53.040
Noriko!

558
01:00:55.334 --> 01:00:56.876
Nori...

559
01:02:33.542 --> 01:02:36.336
<i>Damage wreaked by the giant creature</i>

560
01:02:36.337 --> 01:02:39.379
<i>includes some 30.000 killed and injured</i>

561
01:02:39.380 --> 01:02:42.799
{\an8}<i>and 20.000 homes and buildings destroyed.</i>

562
01:02:42.800 --> 01:02:47.846
{\an8}<i>Recovery operations are underway.
but the path the creature took</i>

563
01:02:47.847 --> 01:02:51.682
<i>carries a risk of radiation that
is impeding progress.</i>

564
01:02:51.683 --> 01:02:57.146
<i>Police have cordoned off central Ginza
to collect shards of the creature</i>

565
01:02:57.730 --> 01:03:03.026
<i>which are of unknown composition
and potentially hazardous.</i>

566
01:03:18.581 --> 01:03:20.291
I'm so sorry.

567
01:03:25.462 --> 01:03:27.213
What now for Akiko?

568
01:03:29.258 --> 01:03:32.093
We pull together. that's what.

569
01:03:32.677 --> 01:03:33.802
Hey. Akiko.

570
01:03:36.681 --> 01:03:41.810
You like playing with me
when Dad's away at work. right?

571
01:03:42.477 --> 01:03:44.395
Where's Mommy?

572
01:03:50.441 --> 01:03:55.613
Mommy had to go away
for a little while for work.

573
01:03:56.238 --> 01:03:58.700
But you'll have me with you. okay?

574
01:04:45.531 --> 01:04:48.783
You can't forgive me. Is that it?

575
01:04:55.539 --> 01:04:56.624
It's my fault...

576
01:04:58.500 --> 01:05:00.710
for thinking I could dream again.

577
01:05:15.307 --> 01:05:16.682
Mr. Shikishima.

578
01:05:18.184 --> 01:05:24.022
There's actually a strategy being hatched
to defeat Godzilla...

579
01:05:25.440 --> 01:05:27.150
led by private citizens.

580
01:05:28.193 --> 01:05:30.694
It lacks any real basis for viability.
but...

581
01:05:34.031 --> 01:05:35.490
will you take part?

582
01:05:42.037 --> 01:05:45.499
SPECIAL DISASTER COUNTERMEASURE HEARING

583
01:05:51.088 --> 01:05:54.505
- Wait. everyone here is...
- Yes.

584
01:05:54.506 --> 01:05:57.176
- Ex-navy personnel.
- You're informed.

585
01:05:57.676 --> 01:05:58.635
Really?

586
01:06:17.401 --> 01:06:21.947
{\an8}I'm Captain Hotta. formerly of
the Yukikaze Destroyer.

587
01:06:22.447 --> 01:06:25.907
As you all know. Tokyo again faces...

588
01:06:25.908 --> 01:06:30.369
an unprecedented crisis.
This time. a monster attack.

589
01:06:30.370 --> 01:06:35.957
But we have no defense apparatus
of our own to protect our people.

590
01:06:35.958 --> 01:06:41.921
{\an8}What's more. any GHQ-led military action
runs the risk of escalating

591
01:06:41.922 --> 01:06:43.464
{\an8}US-Soviet tensions.

592
01:06:44.591 --> 01:06:50.346
In short. we must confront the monster
with our strengths as private citizens.

593
01:06:51.764 --> 01:06:54.682
This is why we've gathered you here.

594
01:06:54.683 --> 01:06:58.560
{\an8}But we've negotiated
the use of four destroyers

595
01:06:58.561 --> 01:07:01.647
{\an8}originally slated for handover to the UN.

596
01:07:03.441 --> 01:07:04.941
Are you saying...

597
01:07:05.650 --> 01:07:07.694
you want us back on navy ships?

598
01:07:07.695 --> 01:07:10.155
I saw what it did in Ginza.

599
01:07:10.655 --> 01:07:12.530
There's no way to defeat it.

600
01:07:12.531 --> 01:07:16.784
Especially from boats
that have been disarmed.

601
01:07:16.785 --> 01:07:18.118
You're dreaming!

602
01:07:18.119 --> 01:07:22.248
That's what I'm here to explain
if you'll allow.

603
01:07:22.832 --> 01:07:24.040
Mr. Noda?

604
01:07:25.167 --> 01:07:26.002
The plan...

605
01:07:29.171 --> 01:07:30.296
Pardon me.

606
01:07:31.465 --> 01:07:36.301
The plan was drafted by me.
Kenji Noda. ex-Navy technical officer.

607
01:07:36.302 --> 01:07:38.679
The first thing to know

608
01:07:39.221 --> 01:07:44.016
is that this creature the people
of Odo Island call "Godzilla"

609
01:07:44.017 --> 01:07:47.643
cannot be hurt by
conventional weaponry.

610
01:07:47.644 --> 01:07:53.064
I saw it take heavy artillery fire
from the guns of the Takao

611
01:07:53.065 --> 01:07:55.068
and quickly heal itself.

612
01:07:57.528 --> 01:07:59.111
Quiet. please.

613
01:07:59.112 --> 01:08:02.116
So we need a totally different approach.

614
01:08:04.159 --> 01:08:07.161
Let me give you a demonstration.

615
01:08:07.162 --> 01:08:10.413
This is ocean salinity water.

616
01:08:10.414 --> 01:08:15.584
This wood model is weighted down
just enough to barely float.

617
01:08:15.585 --> 01:08:20.506
What happens if we pipe in freon gas.
enveloping it in bubbles?

618
01:08:20.507 --> 01:08:25.010
That's easy. Bubbles or not.
it would stay afloat.

619
01:08:27.387 --> 01:08:28.971
That's what you'd think.

620
01:08:35.727 --> 01:08:36.938
It sinks!

621
01:08:39.189 --> 01:08:43.692
The freon bubbles prevent the model
from contacting the seawater.

622
01:08:43.693 --> 01:08:49.240
My idea is to entrap Godzilla like this
and sink it to the ocean floor.

623
01:08:49.824 --> 01:08:53.991
Did you have any idea
Doc was such a bigwig?

624
01:08:53.992 --> 01:08:55.203
No.

625
01:09:07.797 --> 01:09:10.384
At over 1.500 meters in depth.

626
01:09:10.385 --> 01:09:14.975
the Sagami Trench is
the deepest place in nearby waters.

627
01:09:14.976 --> 01:09:20.402
The plan is to strap freon cylinders
to Godzilla and let them foam.

628
01:09:20.403 --> 01:09:22.530
We'll create a bubble membrane.

629
01:09:22.531 --> 01:09:27.290
It'll sink so rapidly that
the pressure will crush it.

630
01:09:30.588 --> 01:09:33.050
We'll kill it with the power of the sea.

631
01:09:33.968 --> 01:09:37.474
That's the outline
for Operation Wada Tsumi.

632
01:09:38.727 --> 01:09:42.526
It's of the sea.
Won't it withstand the pressure?

633
01:09:43.903 --> 01:09:50.456
After 25 seconds. every square meter
will apply 1.500 tons of pressure.

634
01:09:50.457 --> 01:09:55.924
Even ocean-born creatures cannot bear
such rapid pressure changes.

635
01:09:55.925 --> 01:09:56.842
Can you promise...

636
01:09:58.053 --> 01:10:00.224
that would kill Godzilla?

637
01:10:02.770 --> 01:10:06.025
Godzilla is an unknown organism.

638
01:10:06.026 --> 01:10:08.238
We can only predict what will happen.

639
01:10:12.329 --> 01:10:14.832
But this is our best alternative.

640
01:10:14.833 --> 01:10:17.128
Will it kill it? Or will it not?

641
01:10:20.134 --> 01:10:22.096
I can't absolutely guarantee it.

642
01:10:24.643 --> 01:10:25.477
Shikishima!

643
01:10:26.062 --> 01:10:27.481
It can be done!

644
01:10:32.740 --> 01:10:33.741
Mr. Shikishima.

645
01:10:35.412 --> 01:10:36.914
Hear me out. please.

646
01:10:54.237 --> 01:10:57.117
Now. let's get to the details.

647
01:11:01.959 --> 01:11:06.051
Two ships will corral Godzilla
and wrap it in cable.

648
01:11:06.885 --> 01:11:12.771
The cable will have multiple
freon gas cylinders attached to it.

649
01:11:14.899 --> 01:11:18.322
The gas will be released
as it's being tied.

650
01:11:19.449 --> 01:11:23.663
And Godzilla will take
a rapid plunge of 1.500 meters.

651
01:11:23.664 --> 01:11:25.334
What if that fails?

652
01:11:25.335 --> 01:11:27.004
There is a Plan B.

653
01:11:28.297 --> 01:11:31.261
Look into the courtyard.

654
01:11:49.837 --> 01:11:50.963
Inflate!

655
01:11:56.348 --> 01:11:58.977
I'm Itagaki of Toyo Balloon.

656
01:11:58.978 --> 01:12:00.689
What you just saw

657
01:12:00.690 --> 01:12:04.612
is an inflatable flotation device
like the kind...

658
01:12:04.613 --> 01:12:06.699
used in navy aircraft.

659
01:12:06.700 --> 01:12:12.043
CO2 is shot into air sacs for buoyancy.
like a life preserver.

660
01:12:13.838 --> 01:12:15.841
When Godzilla hits the bottom.
we raise it right back to the surface.

661
01:12:15.842 --> 01:12:19.471
we quickly raise it back up
to the surface.

662
01:12:19.472 --> 01:12:26.108
If it can bear the pressure. it'll then
contend with massive decompression.

663
01:12:26.109 --> 01:12:30.491
I can't say for sure
that it wouldn't survive.

664
01:12:30.492 --> 01:12:32.914
But we must do what we can.

665
01:12:38.256 --> 01:12:41.011
You've all survived a tragic war.

666
01:12:41.012 --> 01:12:45.978
So it pains me to ask you again
to put your lives on the line.

667
01:12:45.979 --> 01:12:49.108
But understand this.

668
01:12:49.109 --> 01:12:52.907
We can't rely on the US
or Japanese governments.

669
01:12:52.908 --> 01:12:56.288
So the future of this country
is in our hands.

670
01:12:59.336 --> 01:13:00.421
I can't do it.

671
01:13:02.466 --> 01:13:04.386
I have a family.

672
01:13:04.387 --> 01:13:07.350
And that goes for most people here.

673
01:13:08.101 --> 01:13:12.067
Why are we always the ones
drawing the short straw?

674
01:13:13.278 --> 01:13:15.699
We got enough of that in the war.

675
01:13:21.960 --> 01:13:23.169
Please.

676
01:13:23.170 --> 01:13:26.259
I beg you to listen very carefully.

677
01:13:26.926 --> 01:13:32.520
This is not an order.
You're all free to leave if you wish.

678
01:13:33.105 --> 01:13:36.527
We have no right to stop you.

679
01:14:00.612 --> 01:14:01.781
This plan...

680
01:14:03.284 --> 01:14:05.287
does it mean certain death?

681
01:14:06.289 --> 01:14:07.707
Of course not.

682
01:14:10.129 --> 01:14:13.301
Then it definitely beats wartime.

683
01:14:16.265 --> 01:14:17.518
It can't be helped.

684
01:14:18.936 --> 01:14:20.981
Someone has to do it.

685
01:14:20.982 --> 01:14:23.652
Who can sail the ships if not us?

686
01:14:23.653 --> 01:14:24.738
- Yeah.
- That's right.

687
01:14:25.865 --> 01:14:29.414
Well. then! Are we in. boys?

688
01:14:38.053 --> 01:14:39.098
My friends...

689
01:14:41.476 --> 01:14:42.311
thank you.

690
01:14:43.480 --> 01:14:44.733
Hear. hear!

691
01:14:52.204 --> 01:14:57.755
{\an8}What a surprise. to find you're
the mastermind of such a grand plan.

692
01:14:57.756 --> 01:15:00.802
{\an8}Well. I've had a direct encounter with it.

693
01:15:00.803 --> 01:15:03.599
So the task fell to me.

694
01:15:03.600 --> 01:15:07.104
And we were called for the same reason.

695
01:15:07.105 --> 01:15:10.361
Do you think Godzilla will return?

696
01:15:11.489 --> 01:15:14.577
I think we can assume that Godzilla

697
01:15:14.578 --> 01:15:17.832
has added Tokyo to "its territory".

698
01:15:17.833 --> 01:15:22.883
I expect it'll be back
within ten days at the latest.

699
01:15:22.884 --> 01:15:24.135
That soon?

700
01:15:24.136 --> 01:15:27.141
You set up radiation-detecting buoys?

701
01:15:27.142 --> 01:15:30.230
Visual detection isn't enough.

702
01:15:30.231 --> 01:15:34.988
How can you expect it
to walk right into your trap?

703
01:15:34.989 --> 01:15:37.408
- I can't.
- What. no plan?

704
01:15:37.409 --> 01:15:41.334
{\an8}Who do you think I am?
Of course. I have a plan.

705
01:15:43.755 --> 01:15:46.634
{\an8}We have acoustic minesweepers.

706
01:15:46.635 --> 01:15:51.434
We use the speakers to play
a recording of Godzilla's voice.

707
01:15:51.435 --> 01:15:53.561
{\an8}- Its voice?
- Yeah.

708
01:15:53.562 --> 01:15:58.147
{\an8}It'll see it
as another territorial competitor.

709
01:15:58.773 --> 01:16:00.690
{\an8}- Hopefully.
- Hopefully?

710
01:16:00.691 --> 01:16:02.525
{\an8}You don't instill confidence.

711
01:16:02.526 --> 01:16:05.734
{\an8}And that flotation device?

712
01:16:05.735 --> 01:16:08.736
{\an8}I can't envision that working well.

713
01:16:08.737 --> 01:16:10.862
{\an8}Any other ideas then?

714
01:16:10.863 --> 01:16:14.282
I know! We pull it up with the destroyers.

715
01:16:14.283 --> 01:16:19.786
{\an8}Godzilla weighs some 20.000 tons.
too heavy for two destroyers.

716
01:16:20.786 --> 01:16:21.912
Oh.

717
01:16:22.912 --> 01:16:26.415
{\an8}In short. your plan is full of holes.

718
01:16:27.165 --> 01:16:31.002
{\an8}If you have a better one. let's hear it.

719
01:16:33.210 --> 01:16:34.295
{\an8}Mr. Noda.

720
01:16:36.254 --> 01:16:39.631
Can you get ahold of a fighter plane?

721
01:16:40.548 --> 01:16:41.631
Fighter plane?

722
01:16:41.632 --> 01:16:46.467
I could anger it with gunfire
and draw it to Sagami Bay.

723
01:16:46.468 --> 01:16:50.013
All planes were decommissioned.

724
01:16:50.638 --> 01:16:54.306
Even if you could. it shoots a heat ray.

725
01:16:54.307 --> 01:16:57.266
You'd risk your life flying so close.

726
01:16:57.267 --> 01:16:59.309
I'll take that risk.

727
01:16:59.310 --> 01:17:02.603
A fighter plane is nimbler than a boat.

728
01:17:02.604 --> 01:17:07.023
You're not aiming to get shot down.
are you?

729
01:17:07.815 --> 01:17:09.482
Do you have a death wish?

730
01:17:11.150 --> 01:17:11.984
You're drunk.

731
01:17:12.568 --> 01:17:15.069
You just want to avenge Noriko.

732
01:17:16.153 --> 01:17:17.278
Got a problem with that?

733
01:17:17.279 --> 01:17:19.280
It's too late.

734
01:17:21.448 --> 01:17:24.700
You should've married her before!

735
01:17:25.326 --> 01:17:27.075
You knew how she felt.

736
01:17:27.076 --> 01:17:30.078
Don't you think I wanted that too?

737
01:17:30.996 --> 01:17:33.331
Then why didn't you?

738
01:17:35.081 --> 01:17:36.374
Because...

739
01:17:42.794 --> 01:17:45.254
my war isn't over yet.

740
01:18:10.353 --> 01:18:12.853
- You found a plane?
- Yes.

741
01:18:12.854 --> 01:18:15.064
But it's a unique one.

742
01:18:34.200 --> 01:18:39.244
The short-range interceptor Shinden
was built at war's end.

743
01:18:40.454 --> 01:18:42.954
It was designed to shoot down bombers.

744
01:18:42.955 --> 01:18:45.581
and reach speeds of over 400 knots.

745
01:18:45.582 --> 01:18:50.959
Its canard design and four
30-mm guns pack a punch.

746
01:18:50.960 --> 01:18:54.380
It's a plane full of innovations.

747
01:18:54.880 --> 01:18:59.298
Only a few prototypes were field deployed.

748
01:18:59.299 --> 01:19:06.053
They were kept here
for a mainland battle that never came.

749
01:19:06.595 --> 01:19:10.555
They were left to rust
and are in bad shape.

750
01:19:11.723 --> 01:19:14.140
It's not airworthy as is.

751
01:19:14.141 --> 01:19:17.267
What we need is a top mechanic.

752
01:19:17.268 --> 01:19:21.312
someone who knows their way
around a fighter plane.

753
01:19:23.814 --> 01:19:27.482
I know just the person.

754
01:19:30.026 --> 01:19:32.859
{\an8}Ex-Odo Island detachment mechanic?

755
01:19:32.860 --> 01:19:35.320
- Sosaku Tachibana?
- Yes.

756
01:19:35.321 --> 01:19:38.364
Tachibana.

757
01:19:39.781 --> 01:19:42.199
No known current address.

758
01:19:42.200 --> 01:19:46.410
- I see.
- We're swamped with search requests.

759
01:19:46.411 --> 01:19:48.661
This will take time.

760
01:19:48.662 --> 01:19:51.662
I need to locate him urgently.

761
01:19:51.663 --> 01:19:54.540
There's not much more I can do.

762
01:19:54.541 --> 01:19:56.749
- I beg you. please!
- What?

763
01:19:56.750 --> 01:19:59.376
The country's future depends on it!

764
01:19:59.377 --> 01:20:02.544
I'm sure. but I can't do the impossible.

765
01:20:02.545 --> 01:20:03.462
Sorry.

766
01:20:03.463 --> 01:20:05.214
Well then...

767
01:20:05.715 --> 01:20:10.384
where was he posted before Odo Island?

768
01:20:17.847 --> 01:20:20.263
I've asked everywhere.

769
01:20:20.264 --> 01:20:24.517
But this Tachibana
probably doesn't want to be found.

770
01:20:25.517 --> 01:20:28.269
We can find another mechanic.

771
01:20:28.270 --> 01:20:30.270
Any other leads?

772
01:20:30.271 --> 01:20:32.063
Just wait a bit longer.

773
01:20:33.773 --> 01:20:36.398
Why must it be him?

774
01:20:36.399 --> 01:20:40.569
- Godzilla can come at any time.
- It has to be Tachibana!

775
01:20:41.236 --> 01:20:43.903
He's going to get my message.

776
01:20:44.571 --> 01:20:46.239
Please!

777
01:21:12.629 --> 01:21:14.380
Tachibana.

778
01:21:15.673 --> 01:21:19.049
Mr. Tachibana! It's really you!

779
01:21:22.927 --> 01:21:24.762
What's this about?

780
01:21:28.639 --> 01:21:29.723
Wait.

781
01:21:32.141 --> 01:21:36.852
The Odo Island massacre was all my fault?!

782
01:21:38.728 --> 01:21:40.480
Are you serious?

783
01:21:41.105 --> 01:21:42.522
I'm sorry.

784
01:21:43.190 --> 01:21:48.733
I knew if I angered you.
you'd come find me.

785
01:21:48.734 --> 01:21:49.735
How dare you!

786
01:21:52.570 --> 01:21:54.529
The Ginza attack...

787
01:21:55.572 --> 01:21:56.907
was the same as Odo.

788
01:21:58.240 --> 01:21:59.949
It was Godzilla.

789
01:22:07.871 --> 01:22:11.789
I need you to repair a fighter for me.

790
01:22:11.790 --> 01:22:13.791
so I can kill it!

791
01:22:14.584 --> 01:22:19.710
I needed to find you.
to ask for your help.

792
01:22:19.711 --> 01:22:22.588
That's why I wrote those letters.

793
01:22:24.380 --> 01:22:25.964
Please forgive me!

794
01:22:31.635 --> 01:22:33.094
You're on your own.

795
01:22:34.429 --> 01:22:36.472
I'm not helping you.

796
01:22:37.222 --> 01:22:40.473
No. wait. Mr. Tachibana!

797
01:22:40.474 --> 01:22:45.268
Please listen to me!
I need your help to kill Godzilla.

798
01:22:45.269 --> 01:22:49.270
It's something only you can do.

799
01:22:50.980 --> 01:22:55.690
I exploded a mine in its mouth.
and that hurt it more than a ship's guns.

800
01:22:55.691 --> 01:22:58.527
It's vulnerable from the inside.
You get me?

801
01:23:00.945 --> 01:23:02.071
You don't mean...

802
01:23:03.488 --> 01:23:08.783
I can kill it if I fly a plane
full of explosives into its mouth.

803
01:23:15.703 --> 01:23:16.913
Kamikaze...

804
01:23:19.456 --> 01:23:21.290
The war isn't over...

805
01:23:24.125 --> 01:23:26.252
for you either.

806
01:23:29.462 --> 01:23:33.421
- You got that injury by falling down?
- Ow.

807
01:23:33.422 --> 01:23:37.215
It's swelling up like a grapefruit.

808
01:23:37.216 --> 01:23:40.218
It's embarrassing. but I was drunk.

809
01:23:40.219 --> 01:23:42.426
I barely remember it.

810
01:23:42.427 --> 01:23:47.848
I guess you deserved to celebrate
after finding Mr. Tachibana.

811
01:23:48.849 --> 01:23:50.809
A canard. huh?

812
01:23:51.934 --> 01:23:54.477
I'd heard rumors.
but they actually did it.

813
01:23:56.770 --> 01:23:58.687
Mr. Tachibana.

814
01:23:58.688 --> 01:24:01.147
Thank you all for coming!

815
01:24:01.148 --> 01:24:03.316
You're Mr. Tachibana?

816
01:24:06.818 --> 01:24:11.528
So this is the phantom
short-range interceptor Shinden?

817
01:24:11.529 --> 01:24:14.406
Can you make this fly?

818
01:24:17.491 --> 01:24:20.242
We'll do all we can.

819
01:24:20.243 --> 01:24:21.743
Thank you.

820
01:24:22.786 --> 01:24:25.288
Good luck. Good luck.

821
01:24:43.632 --> 01:24:44.924
What's wrong?

822
01:24:45.550 --> 01:24:48.885
Brighten up. Mastermind.
It's bad for morale.

823
01:24:48.886 --> 01:24:50.802
I know it's my plan.

824
01:24:50.803 --> 01:24:55.179
But I'm feeling we'll need
a miracle to make it work.

825
01:24:55.180 --> 01:25:00.016
Doing nothing won't cause
a miracle either.

826
01:25:00.017 --> 01:25:01.351
You're right.

827
01:25:02.059 --> 01:25:05.186
Take a look at these guys' faces.

828
01:25:06.521 --> 01:25:08.313
They're not stupid.

829
01:25:08.314 --> 01:25:11.440
They know they're risking their lives.

830
01:25:12.483 --> 01:25:13.567
And yet...

831
01:25:14.650 --> 01:25:18.068
their faces are beaming.

832
01:25:18.069 --> 01:25:23.072
They're happy. This time.
they'll make a difference.

833
01:25:24.032 --> 01:25:26.575
Make a difference.

834
01:25:28.117 --> 01:25:30.660
We all came through war.

835
01:25:31.244 --> 01:25:34.996
This time. we're making it right.

836
01:25:46.794 --> 01:25:50.087
2F CONFERENCE ROOM 3.
SPECIAL DISASTER COUNTERMEASURE HQ

837
01:25:50.088 --> 01:25:51.006
Hurry up!

838
01:25:54.342 --> 01:25:55.759
Make room.

839
01:25:57.092 --> 01:26:00.636
One hour ago. east of Hachijo Island.

840
01:26:00.637 --> 01:26:04.930
33.10 North. 140.01 East.

841
01:26:04.931 --> 01:26:09.058
we got Geiger readings from multiple buoys

842
01:26:09.059 --> 01:26:10.183
followed by...

843
01:26:10.184 --> 01:26:12.186
here and here.

844
01:26:28.070 --> 01:26:29.738
Godzilla's coming.

845
01:26:30.571 --> 01:26:32.072
{\an8}At last.

846
01:26:32.073 --> 01:26:37.408
{\an8}At this rate. it's due to arrive
over the Sagami Trench

847
01:26:37.409 --> 01:26:40.201
{\an8}at 1100 hours tomorrow. which means

848
01:26:40.202 --> 01:26:44.413
{\an8}we have to mobilize
and be in positions by 0800.

849
01:26:46.373 --> 01:26:47.332
But tell me...

850
01:26:47.333 --> 01:26:50.291
will your device be ready by then?

851
01:26:51.709 --> 01:26:53.626
Take us with you.

852
01:26:53.627 --> 01:26:56.252
The final three hours will be critical.

853
01:26:56.253 --> 01:26:58.045
We want it to be perfect.

854
01:26:58.046 --> 01:27:01.715
But you could get caught in the fight.

855
01:27:02.674 --> 01:27:04.968
We've all seen war too.

856
01:27:10.721 --> 01:27:17.642
Then everybody. go home tonight.
Spend the time with your families.

857
01:27:19.267 --> 01:27:20.685
You mean... be prepared?

858
01:27:25.854 --> 01:27:27.272
Come to think of it...

859
01:27:28.147 --> 01:27:32.942
this country has treated life
far too cheaply.

860
01:27:33.859 --> 01:27:36.112
Poorly armored tanks.

861
01:27:36.820 --> 01:27:43.116
poor supply chains resulting in half
of all deaths from starvation and disease.

862
01:27:44.408 --> 01:27:49.577
fighter planes built
without ejection seats.

863
01:27:50.577 --> 01:27:55.164
and finally. kamikaze and suicide attacks.

864
01:27:57.124 --> 01:27:59.458
That's why this time...

865
01:28:00.876 --> 01:28:03.502
I'd take pride in a citizen-led effort...

866
01:28:05.254 --> 01:28:08.505
that sacrifices no lives at all!

867
01:28:10.173 --> 01:28:12.258
This next battle...

868
01:28:13.009 --> 01:28:15.093
is not one waged to the death...

869
01:28:16.386 --> 01:28:19.137
but a battle to live for the future.

870
01:28:23.306 --> 01:28:28.268
Let's do it!

871
01:28:31.561 --> 01:28:34.187
Finally. tomorrow's the day.

872
01:28:34.188 --> 01:28:35.312
I can't wait.

873
01:28:35.313 --> 01:28:37.064
You're not going.

874
01:28:39.442 --> 01:28:40.358
What do you mean?

875
01:28:40.359 --> 01:28:43.943
Well. you're useless
with that arm. anyway.

876
01:28:44.444 --> 01:28:46.362
Even Shikishima's going!

877
01:28:46.904 --> 01:28:49.195
Because I'm not a veteran?

878
01:28:49.196 --> 01:28:50.904
I can be useful.

879
01:28:50.905 --> 01:28:54.158
Not having been to war...

880
01:28:54.908 --> 01:28:57.119
is something to be proud of.

881
01:29:03.581 --> 01:29:05.874
I want to defend my country too.

882
01:29:09.168 --> 01:29:11.335
Take me with you!

883
01:29:13.669 --> 01:29:16.630
We've been a team for a long time!

884
01:29:18.214 --> 01:29:19.631
I'm begging you!

885
01:29:20.674 --> 01:29:22.259
Take me with you!

886
01:29:23.092 --> 01:29:24.800
I want to go with you!

887
01:29:24.801 --> 01:29:27.511
We leave you the future.

888
01:29:27.512 --> 01:29:29.262
Captain!

889
01:29:29.263 --> 01:29:30.805
Mr. Noda!

890
01:29:42.103 --> 01:29:43.812
A little lower.

891
01:29:44.354 --> 01:29:45.564
Careful.

892
01:30:01.324 --> 01:30:04.284
Here you go. Akiko.

893
01:30:12.872 --> 01:30:13.831
I want to...

894
01:30:14.457 --> 01:30:17.708
thank you for everything.

895
01:30:31.008 --> 01:30:32.384
Akiko.

896
01:30:33.302 --> 01:30:34.927
Did you have fun with Auntie?

897
01:30:34.928 --> 01:30:36.385
It was fun.

898
01:30:36.386 --> 01:30:39.055
Good. I'm glad.

899
01:30:43.349 --> 01:30:44.642
Is that for me?

900
01:30:46.518 --> 01:30:47.684
Thank you.

901
01:30:53.355 --> 01:30:55.480
- Akiko?
- Hmm?

902
01:30:55.481 --> 01:30:59.984
Is this you. me and Mom?

903
01:31:01.110 --> 01:31:03.320
That's Mom there.

904
01:31:04.612 --> 01:31:05.904
I see.

905
01:31:07.113 --> 01:31:08.657
It's really good.

906
01:31:19.455 --> 01:31:21.413
Why do you look sad?

907
01:31:26.334 --> 01:31:28.084
What's wrong?

908
01:31:28.085 --> 01:31:29.418
Akiko.

909
01:31:30.210 --> 01:31:32.546
There. there.

910
01:31:34.213 --> 01:31:39.299
It'll be all right. I'm not leaving you.

911
01:32:55.637 --> 01:32:56.930
Mr. Tachibana.

912
01:32:58.930 --> 01:32:59.974
Is it ready?

913
01:33:03.809 --> 01:33:05.143
Give me a minute.

914
01:33:17.025 --> 01:33:18.610
The bomb you ordered.

915
01:33:19.986 --> 01:33:24.696
Two machine guns. 140kg... 120 rounds. 80kg...

916
01:33:24.697 --> 01:33:27.364
and one main fuel tank. 400kg. removed.

917
01:33:27.990 --> 01:33:32.576
Instead. a No. 25 bomb in the nose
and a No. 50 in the fuselage.

918
01:33:34.244 --> 01:33:37.163
Now. I can finally pay them back.

919
01:33:51.338 --> 01:33:52.755
That's funny.

920
01:33:57.175 --> 01:33:59.343
Part of me wants to live.

921
01:34:03.970 --> 01:34:06.430
Same as all the men that day.

922
01:34:07.681 --> 01:34:09.641
They all wanted to go home.

923
01:34:11.100 --> 01:34:16.645
But instead. they got squashed like bugs.

924
01:34:18.271 --> 01:34:20.064
I understand.

925
01:34:43.119 --> 01:34:45.495
This was drawn by a girl named Akiko.

926
01:34:47.497 --> 01:34:49.623
I want to protect her future.

927
01:34:53.960 --> 01:34:57.503
I will stop Godzilla no matter what.

928
01:34:58.462 --> 01:35:00.797
You're finally ready.

929
01:35:02.924 --> 01:35:06.803
Then. this is important.

930
01:35:07.469 --> 01:35:08.679
Look here.

931
01:35:09.805 --> 01:35:11.890
The bombs' safety.

932
01:35:12.516 --> 01:35:14.307
Pull it right before flying in.

933
01:35:14.308 --> 01:35:15.810
Got it?

934
01:35:17.478 --> 01:35:18.729
One more thing.

935
01:35:28.989 --> 01:35:30.239
Akiko.

936
01:35:32.408 --> 01:35:35.202
Are you all by yourself?

937
01:35:36.120 --> 01:35:37.245
Look.

938
01:35:44.209 --> 01:35:45.837
{\an8}TO SUMIKO...

939
01:35:58.347 --> 01:36:02.809
LOOK AFTER AKIKO.
USE THIS MONEY FOR HER.

940
01:36:10.275 --> 01:36:12.901
From Daddy?

941
01:36:13.569 --> 01:36:17.238
Huh? Yeah. from Daddy.

942
01:36:18.114 --> 01:36:20.532
It's all right. Don't worry.

943
01:36:37.714 --> 01:36:42.301
This is Kuroshio 12.
35.03 North. 139.41 East.

944
01:36:42.302 --> 01:36:44.053
Many deep-sea fish found!

945
01:37:02.904 --> 01:37:08.531
<i>Godzilla sighted in Sagami Bay!</i>

946
01:37:08.532 --> 01:37:11.868
<i>Underwater guidance decoy activated!</i>

947
01:37:11.869 --> 01:37:14.789
Take only essentials with you!

948
01:37:15.664 --> 01:37:16.956
Hurry and get aboard!

949
01:37:16.957 --> 01:37:19.000
Let's get a move on.

950
01:37:20.627 --> 01:37:22.419
Mizushima took our advice?

951
01:37:22.420 --> 01:37:24.253
It's the best thing for him.

952
01:37:24.254 --> 01:37:27.174
I didn't want Shikishima to fly either.

953
01:37:27.175 --> 01:37:30.634
A failed kamikaze pilot? It worries me.

954
01:37:30.635 --> 01:37:33.930
He's got Akiko. He'll make it back alive.

955
01:37:44.105 --> 01:37:46.774
<i>Underwater decoy team destroyed!</i>

956
01:37:46.775 --> 01:37:52.363
<i>Godzilla has entered Sagami Bay!
Wada Tsumi ships. leave port now!</i>

957
01:37:52.863 --> 01:37:53.947
Look.

958
01:37:54.864 --> 01:37:56.073
There!

959
01:37:56.074 --> 01:37:58.118
It's already here?

960
01:38:09.169 --> 01:38:13.089
<i>Godzilla's through the final defense line!
Heading for shore!</i>

961
01:38:14.173 --> 01:38:15.299
I'm off!

962
01:39:09.513 --> 01:39:14.309
{\an8}Time to end it once and for all.
Shikishima.

963
01:39:14.851 --> 01:39:21.482
<i>Leave port now! Repeat.
Wada Tsumi ships. leave port now!</i>

964
01:39:28.196 --> 01:39:30.906
What now? The plan's ruined!

965
01:39:31.532 --> 01:39:33.533
We set sail anyway.

966
01:39:33.534 --> 01:39:38.662
We need to sink it over Sagami Trench.
or it won't work.

967
01:39:38.663 --> 01:39:42.081
Shikishima will have to lure it!

968
01:39:42.082 --> 01:39:43.250
Move out!

969
01:39:43.251 --> 01:39:44.169
Let's go!

970
01:40:00.516 --> 01:40:02.976
Radio from Mr. Shikishima!

971
01:40:04.352 --> 01:40:09.064
I'm in the air. preparing to lure
Godzilla to the target area.

972
01:40:09.065 --> 01:40:11.232
We'll be ready.

973
01:40:11.233 --> 01:40:12.692
<i>Get there quickly.</i>

974
01:40:12.693 --> 01:40:17.780
Don't do anything rash!
I won't forgive you if you orphan Akiko.

975
01:40:20.867 --> 01:40:22.993
You hear me. Shikishima?

976
01:40:24.495 --> 01:40:26.914
He's ignoring me.

977
01:40:49.725 --> 01:40:51.309
Telegram!

978
01:40:52.561 --> 01:40:53.603
Coming.

979
01:41:00.277 --> 01:41:01.276
Yes?

980
01:41:01.277 --> 01:41:02.861
Mrs. Shikishima?

981
01:41:05.196 --> 01:41:06.865
- Telegram.
- Thanks.

982
01:42:30.313 --> 01:42:33.815
Wow. he's luring it out to sea!

983
01:42:34.483 --> 01:42:37.943
Godzilla looks really ticked off.

984
01:42:37.944 --> 01:42:39.569
It's in pursuit.

985
01:42:39.570 --> 01:42:41.405
Our turn now.

986
01:42:44.408 --> 01:42:48.411
All ships. battle positions!

987
01:42:51.039 --> 01:42:51.955
Freon. ready!

988
01:42:52.540 --> 01:42:55.083
46-cm shells. ready!
Flotation switch . ready!

989
01:42:55.084 --> 01:42:56.709
Cables. ready!

990
01:42:56.710 --> 01:42:59.087
All circuits. ready!

991
01:42:59.088 --> 01:43:02.090
Power on. release safety device!

992
01:43:18.437 --> 01:43:21.190
That's it. Keep coming.

993
01:43:22.608 --> 01:43:26.277
- Team 1. attack as planned.
- As planned!

994
01:43:57.346 --> 01:43:59.724
Attaboy.

995
01:44:36.088 --> 01:44:39.300
That's Godzilla's heat ray.

996
01:44:41.552 --> 01:44:46.847
The ships won't survive this.
All ships must evacuate!

997
01:44:46.848 --> 01:44:48.223
No. this is okay.

998
01:44:48.224 --> 01:44:49.807
Stick to the plan.

999
01:44:49.808 --> 01:44:51.726
But the heat ray!

1000
01:44:51.727 --> 01:44:56.521
Once fired. it takes time to regenerate.

1001
01:44:56.522 --> 01:44:57.983
We go. now!

1002
01:44:58.983 --> 01:45:00.193
Give the order!

1003
01:45:05.697 --> 01:45:07.783
Commence Operation Wada Tsumi!

1004
01:45:26.215 --> 01:45:30.385
Deploy 46-cm shells. freon cylinders.
and flotation device!

1005
01:45:55.865 --> 01:45:57.368
Shikishima!

1006
01:46:23.265 --> 01:46:24.515
Crane deployed!

1007
01:46:24.516 --> 01:46:25.516
Roger!

1008
01:46:26.434 --> 01:46:28.768
Maintain course. Hibiki!

1009
01:46:28.769 --> 01:46:31.187
Hibiki. maintain course!

1010
01:46:31.188 --> 01:46:34.567
Maintain speed. Some damage inevitable.

1011
01:46:38.903 --> 01:46:41.656
Hibiki closing in. 4 meters!

1012
01:46:42.531 --> 01:46:44.032
2 meters!

1013
01:46:44.033 --> 01:46:47.244
- Brace for impact!
- Brace for impact!

1014
01:47:02.132 --> 01:47:06.677
- Crossing complete! Full speed!
- Full speed!

1015
01:47:21.441 --> 01:47:24.151
Yes! Yes!

1016
01:47:24.818 --> 01:47:27.112
- Captain. the switch!
- Roger!

1017
01:47:35.119 --> 01:47:37.496
Oh. no. Not yet?

1018
01:47:38.788 --> 01:47:39.831
Almost.

1019
01:47:49.924 --> 01:47:52.842
Ready...

1020
01:48:02.018 --> 01:48:03.936
Hit it. Captain!

1021
01:48:06.145 --> 01:48:07.773
- Freon!
- Got it!

1022
01:48:24.412 --> 01:48:28.998
Depth 1.200 meters! 1.300 meters!

1023
01:48:29.707 --> 01:48:31.668
- 1.400 meters!
- Keep going!

1024
01:48:31.669 --> 01:48:33.419
- Dive!
- 1.450 meters!

1025
01:48:34.796 --> 01:48:38.591
{\an8}1.500! Target-depth exceeded!

1026
01:48:50.685 --> 01:48:53.519
{\an8}We sunk Godzilla!

1027
01:48:53.520 --> 01:48:54.981
Did it succeed?

1028
01:49:02.736 --> 01:49:04.488
Persistent bastard.

1029
01:49:04.989 --> 01:49:07.616
- Move to Plan B.
- Do it.

1030
01:49:26.090 --> 01:49:27.757
Now rise!

1031
01:49:27.758 --> 01:49:32.804
Depth 1.200 meters!
1.100 meters. 1.000 meters!

1032
01:49:41.521 --> 01:49:42.688
Cables stopped!

1033
01:49:43.522 --> 01:49:45.733
They stopped at 803 meters!

1034
01:49:46.482 --> 01:49:48.819
Why? Why did they stop?

1035
01:49:53.531 --> 01:49:54.949
It chewed through them.

1036
01:49:58.118 --> 01:50:00.578
Hibiki. we'll pull Godzilla up!

1037
01:50:00.579 --> 01:50:02.371
90 degrees. max speed!

1038
01:50:02.372 --> 01:50:04.915
The two ships lack the thrust.

1039
01:50:04.916 --> 01:50:08.502
We've no choice. Give it all you can!

1040
01:50:09.086 --> 01:50:10.295
Yes. sir!

1041
01:50:27.018 --> 01:50:28.770
At this rate.

1042
01:50:28.771 --> 01:50:30.228
the crane won't hold.

1043
01:50:30.229 --> 01:50:31.731
Clear out!

1044
01:50:54.000 --> 01:50:58.670
<i>This is Yokohama Eisen's Fujimaru!</i>

1045
01:50:58.671 --> 01:51:01.255
<i>Doing our best to help!</i>

1046
01:51:01.256 --> 01:51:02.549
That voice.

1047
01:51:03.216 --> 01:51:06.010
Mizushima here. Is that you. Captain?

1048
01:51:07.178 --> 01:51:09.305
Kid. is that you?

1049
01:51:10.223 --> 01:51:11.099
You bet!

1050
01:51:11.100 --> 01:51:14.975
<i>This is Toyo Kisen's Koeimaru.
here to help!</i>

1051
01:51:14.976 --> 01:51:18.646
<i>And Yokohama Eisen's Nikkomaru!
At your service!</i>

1052
01:51:18.647 --> 01:51:20.438
<i>Shiokazemaru. assisting!</i>

1053
01:51:20.439 --> 01:51:21.815
<i>Tetsuyumaru.</i>

1054
01:51:21.816 --> 01:51:23.525
- <i>Nanamimaru.</i>
- <i>Minamimaru.</i>

1055
01:51:23.526 --> 01:51:25.193
- <i>Kisshomaru.</i>
- <i>Junseimaru.</i>

1056
01:51:25.194 --> 01:51:26.527
- <i>Wakamaru.</i>
- <i>Heimitsumaru.</i>

1057
01:51:26.528 --> 01:51:27.946
<i>Tenyumaru</i>.

1058
01:51:27.947 --> 01:51:29.488
- <i>Kaiomaru.</i>
- <i>Hyuga.</i>

1059
01:51:29.489 --> 01:51:30.989
<i>- Choukamaru.
- Shoseimaru.</i>

1060
01:51:30.990 --> 01:51:32.241
- <i>Taramaru.</i>
- <i>Yasakamaru.</i>

1061
01:51:32.242 --> 01:51:35.703
The useless to the rescue!

1062
01:51:38.580 --> 01:51:40.498
I'll be damned.

1063
01:51:40.499 --> 01:51:43.500
I gotta admit I'm glad to see him.

1064
01:51:43.501 --> 01:51:47.254
All you tugboats out there!
Let's catch a Godzilla!

1065
01:51:47.255 --> 01:51:51.383
- Everybody. pull!
- Everybody. pull!

1066
01:52:15.738 --> 01:52:18.699
Godzilla's rising again!

1067
01:52:20.241 --> 01:52:23.660
Come on. show your face!

1068
01:52:23.661 --> 01:52:26.288
Depth 700 meters!

1069
01:52:26.872 --> 01:52:28.958
Keep coming. keep coming!

1070
01:52:59.942 --> 01:53:01.402
It's not damaged enough!

1071
01:53:02.403 --> 01:53:04.530
All ships. evasive action!

1072
01:53:55.366 --> 01:53:56.950
What's he doing?

1073
01:53:56.951 --> 01:53:58.160
No.

1074
01:54:01.997 --> 01:54:04.248
- Don't!
- Stop!

1075
01:54:04.249 --> 01:54:05.792
Shikishima!

1076
01:54:33.066 --> 01:54:34.525
Shikishima...

1077
01:54:49.414 --> 01:54:50.706
No. look!

1078
01:54:55.585 --> 01:54:57.044
I see him.

1079
01:54:58.587 --> 01:55:00.046
I see him!

1080
01:55:02.550 --> 01:55:06.094
<i>Pilot ejected! He's alive!</i>

1081
01:55:14.476 --> 01:55:17.478
This seat has an ejection device.

1082
01:55:18.479 --> 01:55:20.148
Just pull that lever.

1083
01:55:23.859 --> 01:55:25.278
Live.

1084
01:55:27.654 --> 01:55:29.072
Mr. Tachibana.

1085
01:56:59.442 --> 01:57:00.985
Shikishima!

1086
01:57:06.116 --> 01:57:07.408
You did it!

1087
01:57:08.283 --> 01:57:09.326
You did it!

1088
01:57:11.452 --> 01:57:12.704
Kid!

1089
01:57:16.707 --> 01:57:17.542
Sumiko!

1090
01:57:17.543 --> 01:57:18.960
Koichi!

1091
01:57:19.752 --> 01:57:22.295
- Koichi.
- Akiko.

1092
01:57:28.717 --> 01:57:29.719
What?

1093
01:58:11.422 --> 01:58:13.299
Is your war...

1094
01:58:15.425 --> 01:58:16.969
finally over?

1095
01:58:34.399 --> 01:58:35.443
Yes.

1096
01:59:32.825 --> 01:59:37.538
RYUNOSUKE KAMIKI

1097
01:59:39.081 --> 01:59:43.794
MINAMI HAMABE

1098
01:59:45.294 --> 01:59:47.964
YUKI YAMADA

1099
